data.name: label18.Text
data.value:
These all are optional and only extra if you want them.
For best experience it is recommened to include Female Voices and Neo-GK Bannerpack.
Additionaly you can select the backup option which will create backup of Native module.

data.name: label13.Text
data.value:
* Fixes the problem of glowing trees on night maps.
* This shader is still a test version. It could have a few problems.
* Backup shader will be automatically created named "core_shaders (Original).brf". This can later be renamed back to core_shaders.brf if you wish to restore original shaders.

data.name: label12.Text
data.value:
If you have a game going in single player, you won't be able to play it with the module.
To avoid this, you can select the "Backup Native folder" option in previous step. This will create backup folder named "Native (Original)".
Then when you want to go back to play your single player game, rename the NeoGK Native version as something like "Native (NeoGK)" and rename the "Native (Original)" as just "Native". (Whichever version is called just "Native" is the one that will be used when you play the game)

data.name: label27.Text
data.value:
To play the patch, load up Warband and select Native module.
In case anything went wrong during the installation, you can always restore Native module either from backup folder or by using Steam's "Verify integrity of game files".
